Materialism is a plague that has been sweeping through our country for years now. Instead of focusing on the intrinsic things that can give us happiness, we focus on the extrinsic physical objects to give us happiness. Instead of focusing on quality time spent with family, the beauty of nature, etc., we have been conditioned to base our happiness off of how much stuff we have. But, can money truly by happiness? It is the opinion of this paper that, in fact, money cannot buy happiness.
